<item><title>Recreation Centre Gym Equipment Upgrade</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Massey University is seeking quotations from suitably qualified suppliers for the supply, delivery, installation and commissioning of commercial gym equipment for its Recreation Centres located in Auckland, Palmerston North and Wellington.<br /><br />The RFQ consists of multiple equipment lots, including cardio equipment, strength machines, and free weights/accessories. Suppliers may submit responses for one, multiple, or all lots.<br /><br />Suppliers must be able to provide commercial-grade equipment suitable for high-use recreation environments and demonstrate appropriate warranty, servicing, and parts support within New Zealand.<br /><br />Delivery and installation are anticipated between September and December 2026.<br /><br />Full requirements, specifications, and pricing schedules are provided in the RFQ documentation.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Massey University<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 22/Jul/2026 11:00 am (UTC+12:00) Auckland, Wellington time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP2608<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Sport, Recreation Equip, Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.nz/tsi.axd?id=dfee9dd1b0944f9cbece692cedc0cf89s2608s85996a649309434d8b99b28d494b72f0s49</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">dfee9dd1b0944f9cbece692cedc0cf89</guid>
<pubDate>Thu, 02 Jul 2026 02:08:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Sport, Recreation Equip, Services</category>
</item>
<item><title>Enterprise Network Refresh (Solution)</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Massey University is seeking a strategic delivery partner to design, supply, implement, and support a full refresh of its enterprise network infrastructure across all campuses.<br /><br />The solution must address ageing infrastructure, increasing cybersecurity risk, and capacity constraints, delivering a secure, resilient, scalable, and cloud-ready network platform that supports research, teaching, and operational needs.<br /><br />The successful Respondent will provide:<br /><br />•	Network hardware and software platforms<br /><br />•	Design, integration, and implementation services<br /><br />•	Ongoing support and managed services<br /><br />•	A commercial model supporting both capital and service-based approaches (including NaaS)<br /><br />Please note that this RFP (and any contractual commitment) is issued subject to Massey University Council approval of the Network Refresh Business Case (anticipated mid-July 2026).<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Massey University<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 05/Aug/2026 12:00 pm (UTC+12:00) Auckland, Wellington time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP2592<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.nz/tsi.axd?id=a409160d1d1d411f8de7952ebd9a0f98s2592s930449e3ff934542b58ea67687191124s70</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">a409160d1d1d411f8de7952ebd9a0f98</guid>
<pubDate>Wed, 24 Jun 2026 02:42:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>IT &amp; Telecomms</category>
</item>
<item><title>176 Williams Street Kaiapoi seismic strengthening</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Waimakariri District Council is seeking a suitably experienced building contractor to undertake seismic strengthening works at 176 Williams Street, Kaiapoi.<br /><br />The works are to strengthen the existing single-storey retail building to a target seismic rating of 80%NBS, Importance Level 2. The building is will be vacant and stripped out and possession of site is expected to be 17th August 2026<br /><br />The required services include all labour, plant, materials, temporary works, access, coordination, construction management, quality assurance and completion documentation necessary to deliver the strengthening works. The scope includes, but is not limited to, site establishment, protection of existing finishes and services, installation of new structural steel braced frames, roof cross-bracing, portal frame and masonry wall connections, new foundation pads and ground beams, proprietary anchors and bracing systems, making good, testing, inspections and producer statements.<br /><br />The works are to be ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Waimakariri District Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 15/Jul/2026 04:00 pm (UTC+12:00) Auckland, Wellington time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP2579<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 10]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.nz/tsi.axd?id=43c9bb8b9c194760968d17da75376b25s2579s85818252ab0f4a97ad4749bb758701e4s12</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">43c9bb8b9c194760968d17da75376b25</guid>
<pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 02:51:00 GMT</pubDate>
